    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-07T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="837"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/101</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1913-12-07T08:30:00-05:00"
                        notBefore="1913-12-06T00:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                    </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 7, 1914, 8:30 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Your 664, December 2, 678, December 3, and 679, December 3, presented and in the
                    discussion <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> promised to
                    arrange an early conference between him and chief censor and me. He informed me
                    that certain telegrams were stopped because an unnatural number and arrangement
                    of <persName corresp="#p_CX1">Christian</persName> names in them suggested that
                    they concealed a cipher. I shall immediately take up your telegram just come
                    citing welcome specific cablegrams.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
